      "title": "Intensive Forms (صيغ المبالغة)",
      "titleArabic": "صيغ المبالغة",
      "content": [
        "Intensive forms (صيغ المبالغة) are derived from verbs to indicate someone who does an action excessively or habitually.",
        "They emphasize the frequency, intensity, or professionalism of performing an action."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Derived mainly from transitive Form I verbs",
        "Indicates excessive or habitual action",
        "Five main patterns: فَعَّال، فَعُول، فَعِيل، مِفْعَال، فَعَّالَة",
        "Can function as nouns or adjectives"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "أَكَّالٌ", "english": "big eater (one who eats a lot)" },
        { "arabic": "صَبُورٌ", "english": "very patient" },
        { "arabic": "عَلِيمٌ", "english": "all-knowing" },
        { "arabic": "كَذَّابٌ", "english": "habitual liar" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "The Five Main Patterns",
      "titleArabic": "الأوزان الخمسة",
      "content": [
        "Arabic grammarians identified five standard patterns for intensive forms, each conveying exaggeration or habitual action.",
        "These patterns are widely used in classical and modern Arabic."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "فَعَّال: كَذَّاب (liar), سَمَّاع (good listener), غَفَّار (most forgiving)",
        "فَعُول: صَبُور (patient), شَكُور (grateful), غَفُور (forgiving)",
        "فَعِيل: عَلِيم (knowing), سَمِيع (hearing), رَحِيم (merciful)",
        "مِفْعَال: مِعْطَاء (generous giver), مِقْدَام (daring)",
        "فَعِل: حَذِر (cautious), فَطِن (clever)"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "اللهُ غَفُورٌ رَحِيمٌ", "english": "Allah is Most Forgiving, Most Merciful" },
